      "is_quote": false,
      "lang": "en",
      "hashtags": [],
      "mentions": []
    },
    {
      "id": "2036896125232283727",
      "text": "Trying to make founders describe their products in simple everyday language is like trying to push together the north poles of two magnets.",
      "created_at": "Wed Mar 25 20:00:54 +0000 2026",
      "url": "https://twitter.com/paulg/status/2036896125232283727",
      "likes": 2702,
      "retweets": 119,
      "replies": 325,
      "quotes": 55,
      "bookmarks": 394,
      "views": 150033,
      "is_retweet": false,
      "is_reply": false,
      "is_quote": false,
      "lang": "en",
      "hashtags": [],
      "mentions": []
    },
    {
      "id": "2036850752962891993",
      "text": "The thing that will make a VC want to fund you is not how well you match their (claimed) investment thesis. It's the same thing that will make every other VC want to fund you: how well you're doing.",
      "created_at": "Wed Mar 25 17:00:37 +0000 2026",
      "url": "https://twitter.com/paulg/status/2036850752962891993",
      "likes": 1425,
      "retweets": 75,
      "replies": 151,
      "quotes": 20,
      "bookmarks": 359,
      "views": 105593,
      "is_retweet": false,
      "is_reply": false,
      "is_quote": false,
      "lang": "en",
      "hashtags": [],
      "mentions": []
    },
    {
      "id": "2036054489942175864",
      "text": "Someone asked what advice founders ignore. That they:\n\n1. Should change their name.\n\n2. Should launch fast.\n\n3. Shouldn't treat fundraising as success.\n\n4. Shouldn't assume they can raise because it's time to.\n\n5. Should fire bad people quickly.\n\n6. Shouldn't talk to acquirers.",
      "created_at": "Mon Mar 23 12:16:33 +0000 2026",
      "url": "https://twitter.com/paulg/status/2036054489942175864",
      "likes": 4220,
      "retweets": 240,
      "replies": 315,
      "quotes": 59,
      "bookmarks": 2664,
      "views": 915044,
      "is_retweet": false,
      "is_reply": false,
      "is_quote": false,
      "lang": "en",
      "hashtags": [],
      "mentions": []
    },
    {
      "id": "2035981761260273845",
      "text": "I'm the guest on the latest Social Radars episode:\n\nhttps://t.co/xQiAp1QtTg",
      "created_at": "Mon Mar 23 07:27:33 +0000 2026",
      "url": "https://twitter.com/paulg/status/2035981761260273845",
      "likes": 194,
      "retweets": 15,
      "replies": 22,
      "quotes": 1,
      "bookmarks": 72,
      "views": 33353,
      "is_retweet": false,
      "is_reply": false,
      "is_quote": false,
      "lang": "en",
      "hashtags": [],
      "mentions": []
    },
    {
      "id": "2035505992197161397",
      "text": "The Audemars Piguet 2003 movement has a volume of .56 cm³, exactly mid-way between a penny (.43 cm³) and a nickel (.69 cm³). https://t.co/xfL2ffv61l",
      "created_at": "Sat Mar 21 23:57:01 +0000 2026",
      "url": "https://twitter.com/paulg/status/2035505992197161397",
      "likes": 338,
      "retweets": 1,
      "replies": 47,
      "quotes": 3,
      "bookmarks": 28,
      "views": 56360,
      "is_retweet": false,
      "is_reply": false,
      "is_quote": false,
      "lang": "en",
      "hashtags": [],
      "mentions": []
    },
    {
      "id": "2035423991976849854",
      "text": "Whether the next president is a Republican or a Democrat, can we have someone with at least a little class next time? Because this is embarrassing. https://t.co/nbKnxzuh1I",
      "created_at": "Sat Mar 21 18:31:10 +0000 2026",
      "url": "https://twitter.com/paulg/status/2035423991976849854",
      "likes": 19314,
      "retweets": 1394,
      "replies": 1277,
      "quotes": 116,
      "bookmarks": 528,
      "views": 1400004,
      "is_retweet": false,
      "is_reply": false,
      "is_quote": false,
      "lang": "en",
      "hashtags": [],
      "mentions": []
    },
    {
      "id": "2035333989473325185",
      "text": "A bookcase before books started to be shelved in what we now take for granted as the normal way, standing up with their spines outward. That came about 100 years later.",
      "created_at": "Sat Mar 21 12:33:32 +0000 2026",
      "url": "https://twitter.com/paulg/status/2035333989473325185",
      "likes": 368,
      "retweets": 11,
      "replies": 33,
      "quotes": 3,
      "bookmarks": 78,
      "views": 169346,
      "is_retweet": false,
      "is_reply": false,
      "is_quote": true,
      "lang": "en",
      "hashtags": [],
      "mentions": []
    },
    {
      "id": "2035326942530941000",
      "text": "It's extremely valuable not to be influenced by fashion. In just about everything people do, from choosing problems to work on to buying art, there are unfashionable options that are not only better than the fashionable ones, but cheaper too, because they're unfashionable.",
      "created_at": "Sat Mar 21 12:05:32 +0000 2026",
      "url": "https://twitter.com/paulg/status/2035326942530941000",
      "likes": 1868,
      "retweets": 128,
      "replies": 144,
      "quotes": 17,
      "bookmarks": 461,
      "views": 114442,
      "is_retweet": false,
      "is_reply": false,
      "is_quote": false,
      "lang": "en",
      "hashtags": [],
      "mentions": []
    },
    {
      "id": "2035327713137819915",
      "text": "When you're buying things the cheapness is literal. When you're talking about choosing problems to work on, cheapness means they have higher expected value, largely because there's less competition.",
      "created_at": "Sat Mar 21 12:08:36 +0000 2026",
      "url": "https://twitter.com/paulg/status/2035327713137819915",
      "likes": 271,
      "retweets": 6,
      "replies": 15,
      "quotes": 0,
      "bookmarks": 31,
      "views": 38803,
      "is_retweet": false,
      "is_reply": true,
      "is_quote": false,
      "lang": "en",
      "hashtags": [],
      "mentions": []
    },
    {
      "id": "2035328152810008924",
      "text": "At this point whenever I enter a new domain my first instinct is to ask \"what are the options that are undervalued because they're unfashionable?\" There always turn out to be several classes of these. And it's a good way to understand a domain quickly.",
      "created_at": "Sat Mar 21 12:10:20 +0000 2026",
      "url": "https://twitter.com/paulg/status/2035328152810008924",
      "likes": 354,
      "retweets": 10,
      "replies": 21,
      "quotes": 4,
      "bookmarks": 119,
      "views": 37687,
      "is_retweet": false,
      "is_reply": true,
      "is_quote": false,
      "lang": "en",
      "hashtags": [],
      "mentions": []
    },
    {
      "id": "2035325666313310594",
      "text": "I just got a serious email asking if I'd like to book a trip to the moon. Mostly the future hasn't turned out like I expected when I was a kid in the 1970s, but this is exactly what I expected.",
      "created_at": "Sat Mar 21 12:00:28 +0000 2026",
      "url": "https://twitter.com/paulg/status/2035325666313310594",
      "likes": 1898,
      "retweets": 38,
      "replies": 92,
      "quotes": 11,
      "bookmarks": 102,
      "views": 144080,
      "is_retweet": false,
      "is_reply": false,
      "is_quote": false,
      "lang": "en",
      "hashtags": [],
      "mentions": []
    },
    {
      "id": "2035322010562158710",
      "text": "Now before I reply to someone I have to check first that I'm not being baited by an account that spams everyone with AI-generated replies.\n\nCan you write some software to do this check for me @nikitabier?",
      "created_at": "Sat Mar 21 11:45:56 +0000 2026",
      "url": "https://twitter.com/paulg/status/2035322010562158710",
      "likes": 1419,
      "retweets": 18,
      "replies": 209,
      "quotes": 21,
      "bookmarks": 114,
      "views": 222355,
      "is_retweet": false,
      "is_reply": false,
      "is_quote": false,
      "lang": "en",
      "hashtags": [],
      "mentions": [
        "nikitabier"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "2035295243453530365",
      "text": "The fact that AIs tend to answer you in bulleted lists tells us something important, though somewhat depressing: people can't read. They don't do this by accident. What you're seeing is an implicit portrait of the median user.",
      "created_at": "Sat Mar 21 09:59:34 +0000 2026",
      "url": "https://twitter.com/paulg/status/2035295243453530365",
      "likes": 2651,
      "retweets": 141,
      "replies": 467,
