      "mentions": []
    },
    {
      "id": "2034995967842275774",
      "text": "13 yo was very dubious when I told him I got him a watch, but his eyes lit up when he saw what it was. https://t.co/pHradO27dr",
      "created_at": "Fri Mar 20 14:10:21 +0000 2026",
      "url": "https://twitter.com/paulg/status/2034995967842275774",
      "likes": 869,
      "retweets": 3,
      "replies": 91,
      "quotes": 5,
      "bookmarks": 47,
      "views": 59358,
      "is_retweet": false,
      "is_reply": false,
      "is_quote": false,
      "lang": "en",
      "hashtags": [],
      "mentions": []
    },
    {
      "id": "2034937034687524903",
      "text": "Some people criticize Garry, but this excerpt from the latest Social Radars episode is a good example of how insiders feel about how he's doing. The 3 of us in this conversation are 3/5 of YC's board.",
      "created_at": "Fri Mar 20 10:16:11 +0000 2026",
      "url": "https://twitter.com/paulg/status/2034937034687524903",
      "likes": 473,
      "retweets": 12,
      "replies": 45,
      "quotes": 6,
      "bookmarks": 226,
      "views": 140557,
      "is_retweet": false,
      "is_reply": false,
      "is_quote": true,
      "lang": "en",
      "hashtags": [],
      "mentions": []
    },
    {
      "id": "2034924438907494496",
      "text": "Someone asked what past decade seems most similar to the current one. I said the 1930s. Great progress in technology, combined with corrupt, autocratic, populist political leaders.",
      "created_at": "Fri Mar 20 09:26:07 +0000 2026",
      "url": "https://twitter.com/paulg/status/2034924438907494496",
      "likes": 2423,
      "retweets": 160,
      "replies": 160,
      "quotes": 11,
      "bookmarks": 219,
      "views": 124758,
      "is_retweet": false,
      "is_reply": false,
      "is_quote": false,
      "lang": "en",
      "hashtags": [],
      "mentions": []
    },
    {
      "id": "2034756891818004629",
      "text": "If you really want to hold yourself to a high standard, graph the growth rate of the number you care about instead of the number itself. Then you're winning if you can even keep it flat.",
      "created_at": "Thu Mar 19 22:20:21 +0000 2026",
      "url": "https://twitter.com/paulg/status/2034756891818004629",
      "likes": 3275,
      "retweets": 192,
      "replies": 132,
      "quotes": 16,
      "bookmarks": 1470,
      "views": 170483,
      "is_retweet": false,
      "is_reply": false,
      "is_quote": false,
      "lang": "en",
      "hashtags": [],
      "mentions": []
    },
    {
      "id": "2034691852574531846",
      "text": "I'm glad she chose this excerpt about how to make a convincing Demo Day presentation. Founders would be so much more effective at fundraising if they gave their pitches YC-style \"vertebrae\".",
      "created_at": "Thu Mar 19 18:01:55 +0000 2026",
      "url": "https://twitter.com/paulg/status/2034691852574531846",
      "likes": 318,
      "retweets": 10,
      "replies": 32,
      "quotes": 5,
      "bookmarks": 266,
      "views": 61218,
      "is_retweet": false,
      "is_reply": false,
      "is_quote": true,
      "lang": "en",
      "hashtags": [],
      "mentions": []
    },
    {
      "id": "2034676990314225696",
      "text": "Another advantage of focusing on growth rate rather than absolute numbers is that it makes it easier to switch to a new variant of the product if you discover one. It makes it easier to see tails that will eventually wag the dog.",
      "created_at": "Thu Mar 19 17:02:51 +0000 2026",
      "url": "https://twitter.com/paulg/status/2034676990314225696",
      "likes": 1193,
      "retweets": 84,
      "replies": 85,
      "quotes": 6,
      "bookmarks": 364,
      "views": 91745,
      "is_retweet": false,
      "is_reply": false,
      "is_quote": false,
      "lang": "en",
      "hashtags": [],
      "mentions": []
    },
    {
      "id": "2034677503772516820",
      "text": "Example: Your startup is already making millions a year. You discover some new mutation that only makes a couple thousand a week but that's growing by 10% per week. If you focus on growth rates, it will get the attention it should sooner.",
      "created_at": "Thu Mar 19 17:04:54 +0000 2026",
      "url": "https://twitter.com/paulg/status/2034677503772516820",
      "likes": 240,
      "retweets": 8,
      "replies": 9,
      "quotes": 1,
      "bookmarks": 42,
      "views": 29226,
      "is_retweet": false,
      "is_reply": true,
      "is_quote": false,
      "lang": "en",
      "hashtags": [],
      "mentions": []
    },
    {
      "id": "2034678052542713882",
      "text": "It takes a while of course to be sure that the 10% weekly growth rate is real. But if it turns out to be real, and in a market that won't top out, that new revenue source is the one that matters. 10% a week is 142x a year!",
      "created_at": "Thu Mar 19 17:07:04 +0000 2026",
      "url": "https://twitter.com/paulg/status/2034678052542713882",
      "likes": 112,
      "retweets": 4,
      "replies": 11,
      "quotes": 0,
      "bookmarks": 22,
      "views": 22958,
      "is_retweet": false,
      "is_reply": true,
      "is_quote": false,
      "lang": "en",
      "hashtags": [],
      "mentions": []
    },
    {
      "id": "2034655687670702275",
      "text": "There's a vintage watch dealer in London (Somlo) that always has watches in amazing condition. 60 year old watches that seem unworn. I asked the owner how he does it. He said they've been around a long time and always pay promptly, so they get first look.",
      "created_at": "Thu Mar 19 15:38:12 +0000 2026",
      "url": "https://twitter.com/paulg/status/2034655687670702275",
      "likes": 1788,
      "retweets": 17,
      "replies": 67,
      "quotes": 3,
      "bookmarks": 494,
      "views": 277550,
      "is_retweet": false,
      "is_reply": false,
      "is_quote": false,
      "lang": "en",
      "hashtags": [],
      "mentions": []
    },
    {
      "id": "2034646174951481536",
      "text": "This is a really good heuristic. The only downside is that someone will later invent a name for what you do, and you probably won't like it.",
      "created_at": "Thu Mar 19 15:00:24 +0000 2026",
      "url": "https://twitter.com/paulg/status/2034646174951481536",
      "likes": 623,
      "retweets": 24,
      "replies": 39,
      "quotes": 6,
      "bookmarks": 197,
      "views": 77029,
      "is_retweet": false,
      "is_reply": false,
      "is_quote": true,
      "lang": "en",
      "hashtags": [],
      "mentions": []
    },
    {
      "id": "2034645436766503390",
      "text": "If you have multiple kids you might be surprised by how different they look. https://t.co/joBx8BBj7K",
      "created_at": "Thu Mar 19 14:57:28 +0000 2026",
      "url": "https://twitter.com/paulg/status/2034645436766503390",
      "likes": 2100,
      "retweets": 14,
      "replies": 130,
      "quotes": 18,
